<subSubSection lastPageId="244" lastPageNumber="245" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="243" pageNumber="244">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="244" lastPageNumber="245" pageId="243" pageNumber="244">
From 
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M" journalOrPublisher="Revue Francaise d'Entomolgie" pageId="291" pageNumber="292" pagination="154 - 157" title="Hispides nouveaux du Venezuela." volume="1" year="1934">Pic 1934</bibRefCitation>
: Oblong-elongate; subdepressed; shining; testaceous, pronotum with disc brownish, head darker posteriorly, elytral disc greenish-brown; 
<pageBreakToken pageId="244" pageNumber="245" start="start">venter</pageBreakToken>
and legs testaceous. Head: small; sparsely punctate. Antenna: slender. Pronotum: subquadrate; lateral margin straight, rounded anteriorly, slightly canaliculate; anterior angle produced; disc nearly impunctate, irregularly punctate laterally. Scutellum: large. Elytron: lateral margin narrowly margined; apex rounded; punctate-striate; with short carina behind humerus. Total length: 5.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
